JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 576
EP  - 584
VL  - 23
IS  - 6
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper derives quadratic approximations of the standard one-period portfolio selection model under the assumption that means and variances of returns are infinite. Samuelson [Samuelson, P. A. 1970. The fundamental approximation theorem of portfolio analysis in terms of means, variances, and higher moments. Rev. Econom. Stud. 37 (October).], among others, has derived mean-variance approximations when moments are finite; hence, this paper weakens conditions sufficient to obtain quadratic approximations.
AB  - This paper derives quadratic approximations of the standard one-period portfolio selection model under the assumption that means and variances of returns are infinite. Samuelson [Samuelson, P. A. 1970. The fundamental approximation theorem of portfolio analysis in terms of means, variances, and higher moments. Rev. Econom. Stud. 37 (October).], among others, has derived mean-variance approximations when moments are finite; hence, this paper weakens conditions sufficient to obtain quadratic approximations.
